selected_csets.codeset_intention: Create broad and generic general use concept as starting place for research teams and for use in calculating comorbidity indices.  Intent is to only include codes that are specific to this comorbidity category.  Notion of "complicated" (or not) is based on the intention of the Charlson definition of "diabetes with chronic complications."
selected_csets.limitations: May not include certain medications or procedures that may signal a condition. Also note that only standard concepts are included, so should be applied to only the harmonized data. Includes acute complications and other manifestations of diabetes that do not fit in Charlson's notion of "chronic complication". So "uncomplicated" may still be clinically complicated.
selected_csets.provenance: Copy for comparison of container created by UNITEConceptSetBulk@nih.gov on 2023-11-05T17:40:20.287Z. Orig provenance: Selected parent OMOP condition and included descendants (standard codes only).  Apply clinical review result, removed concepts that should not be included.  Incorporates domain team feedback, and represented in a parsimonious concept expression. 1/10/2024 Vocabulary Change removed "autoimmune" diabetes, but otherwise semantically unchanged.
